verses.verse: An Alleluia. Praise the Lord, ye his servants! Praise the name of the Lord.
Let the name of the Lord be blessed; henceforth and forever.
From the rising of the sun to its going down; let the name of the Lord be praised.
The Lord is high over all the nations: his glory is above the heavens.
Who is like the Lord our God who dwelleth on high,
and superintended the things below him in heaven and on the earth?
Who raiseth the distressed from the ground, and lifteth the needy from a dunghill:
to seat him with princes; with the chiefs of his people.
Who settleth the barren woman in a family making her a joyful mother of children.
